Indexed PDF files

Vote up or down on what is interesting. Every vote will help train a machine learning algorithm. The indexed PDFs were obtained as follows:

  • PDF files were downloaded using the UNIX "wget" tool.
  • The PDF files were then converted to raw text using the "pdftotext" tool (ubuntu).
  • A machine learning preprocessor, the "term frequency–inverse document frequency" was used to extract keywords.
  • A minimalistic API was built. The API will accept votes and these votes may be used to train a model.
  • For more information, see the source code at: https://github.com/tommyod/pdf_collector
